    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-07T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-07T20:00:00-05:00" n="594"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94112/405: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-07T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 7, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>526. Reference Shanghai’s 1312, November 27, 5 p.m. Please make an approach to
                    the Japanese Foreign Office, in such manner as you may deem appropriate, and
                    request that the Japanese Government issue instructions to the concerned
                    Japanese naval authorities to release without further delay the American-owned
                    motor vessel <hi rend="italic">Estelle L</hi>., pointing out that this
                    Government does not recognize any right by Japanese naval authorities to apply
                    in China regulations proclaimed by them to vessels under the American flag.<note
                        n="45" xml:id="d594fn45">In accordance with instructions, the Ambassador
                        sent a <hi rend="italic">note verbale to</hi> the Japanese Foreign Ministry,
                        dated December 10.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
